🌺 Concluding Reflection
Dear Friends, I especially love the transition that Sarga 183 is making.
Part One honored the seeker's question.
Part Two established the necessity of reason.
Part Three gently reveals that reason is fulfilled when it turns inward and discovers the ever-present witness.
This is a distinctive feature of the Yoga Vāsiṣṭha: it does not dismiss the intellect. It purifies it until the intellect becomes transparent to Consciousness itself. At that point, knowledge is no longer merely conceptual—it becomes vision.
